parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The expansion or warping of the fuel tank can cause the tank to leak, press against the ignition switch, and affect the handling of the motorcycle, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The fuel tank is expanding or warping
the tank is no longer sitting correctly in the frame
the handlebars hit the tank on turning
the tank presses against the ignition switch
the rubber mounts no longer sit on the frame
the tank is swelling on the sides
and the tank is leaking around the top.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Plastic Gas Tank Swelling and Latch Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The swelling of the plastic gas tank can cause it to not securely latch to the frame, leading to a potential safety hazard while riding, as the tank can become detached and affect the ignition system.
symptoms: the gas tank does not securely latch to the frame
the latch that connects the tank to the frame is obstructed
